So the biggest challenge is

567
00:25:59,480 --> 00:26:02,240
being thin, yet tough.

568
00:26:02,760 --> 00:26:04,520
I want to remind everyone,

569
00:26:05,040 --> 00:26:07,680
don't take this task too lightly.

570
00:26:08,200 --> 00:26:09,520
To make it successful,

571
00:26:09,520 --> 00:26:11,760
without going through some setbacks,

572
00:26:12,000 --> 00:26:13,440
it just won't happen.

573
00:26:13,600 --> 00:26:15,560
Bring out all your skills.

574
00:26:15,560 --> 00:26:17,560
Work with the utmost care.

575
00:26:17,760 --> 00:26:19,600
We'll definitely be able to make it.

576
00:26:20,320 --> 00:26:21,160
Master.

577
00:26:21,520 --> 00:26:22,800
No matter what difficulties we face,

578
00:26:22,800 --> 00:26:24,040
we'll get through them.

579
00:26:28,000 --> 00:26:29,560
Chief Man, how about it?

580
00:26:29,560 --> 00:26:31,160
Will you lead the way?

581
00:26:31,720 --> 00:26:33,800
No way, this has to be you.

582
00:26:33,800 --> 00:26:34,560
Come on now.

583
00:26:35,040 --> 00:26:36,000
Stop arguing.

584
00:26:36,200 --> 00:26:38,840
You know the Beijing Museum order best.

585
00:26:39,440 --> 00:26:40,520
Whatever difficulties come up,

586
00:26:41,240 --> 00:26:42,840
we'll discuss and solve them together.

587
00:26:42,840 --> 00:26:43,280
Alright.

588
00:26:43,280 --> 00:26:45,000
Good, everyone got it?

589
00:26:45,240 --> 00:26:45,600
Understood.

590
00:26:45,600 --> 00:26:46,960
Alright, let's get to work.

591
00:26:54,120 --> 00:26:54,920
Add paper mucilage.

592
00:26:59,320 --> 00:27:00,120
More.

593
00:27:00,200 --> 00:27:01,200
That's already a lot.

594
00:27:01,200 --> 00:27:02,000
More.

595
00:27:03,760 --> 00:27:06,600
Is this mucilage kiwi vine juice?

596
00:27:06,680 --> 00:27:07,480
Yes.

597
00:27:07,880 --> 00:27:09,640
Why add so much of it?

598
00:27:10,560 --> 00:27:11,520
The paper mucilage

599
00:27:11,520 --> 00:27:13,560
serves as a lubricant and suspension agent.

600
00:27:13,680 --> 00:27:14,680
It makes the paper

601
00:27:14,680 --> 00:27:17,520
closer to Chengxintang's smoothness.

602
00:27:18,000 --> 00:27:18,920
The paper's too thin.

603
00:27:19,600 --> 00:27:20,600
If we use too little,

604
00:27:21,040 --> 00:27:22,680
the sheets won't come out even.

605
00:27:23,840 --> 00:27:24,920
Alright, that's enough.

606
00:27:29,720 --> 00:27:31,920
Who holds the screen? Who lifts it?

607
00:27:32,000 --> 00:27:33,040
I can hold the screen.

608
00:27:33,720 --> 00:27:34,520
You?

609
00:27:35,840 --> 00:27:36,440
Ma Gan'er,

610
00:27:37,080 --> 00:27:37,600
you lift the screen.

611
00:27:37,600 --> 00:27:38,080
Okay.

612
00:27:38,200 --> 00:27:39,000
Master Ye.

613
00:27:39,400 --> 00:27:40,280
I can handle it.

614
00:27:40,720 --> 00:27:42,280
This is skilled work.

615
00:27:42,280 --> 00:27:43,480
I can scoop the paper.

616
00:27:43,760 --> 00:27:45,400
You've only scooped paper for a few days.

617
00:27:45,400 --> 00:27:47,040
Without eight or ten years of practice,

618
00:27:47,240 --> 00:27:48,360
this isn't something to fool around with.

619
00:27:49,160 --> 00:27:50,800
Fine, you do it.

620
00:27:50,800 --> 00:27:51,560
Master Ye.

621
00:28:01,880 --> 00:28:02,360
This...

622
00:28:03,800 --> 00:28:04,760
Zhang Du, right?

623
00:28:04,760 --> 00:28:07,280
You hold, and I'll lift for you.

624
00:28:08,360 --> 00:28:10,400
Thank you, Chief Engineer Man.

625
00:28:18,520 --> 00:28:19,320
Look.

626
00:28:20,440 --> 00:28:22,160
Look at the texture of this paper.

627
00:28:23,440 --> 00:28:24,480
Now look at this one.

628
00:28:25,040 --> 00:28:26,480
This is the one we made.

629
00:28:27,400 --> 00:28:28,200
It's thin too.

630
00:28:29,440 --> 00:28:31,600
I'd say these two sheets are pretty similar.

631
00:28:32,200 --> 00:28:33,480
It should count as a pass.

632
00:28:36,440 --> 00:28:37,200
Come, come take a look.

633
00:28:37,200 --> 00:28:38,320
Too many cloud patterns.

634
00:28:39,480 --> 00:28:40,160
It's too coarse.

635
00:28:43,080 --> 00:28:43,640
This...

636
00:28:44,480 --> 00:28:45,600
Still not good enough?

637
00:28:47,240 --> 00:28:51,000
The problem is the pulp isn't fine enough.

638
00:28:52,440 --> 00:28:54,240
I checked the pulp this morning.

639
00:28:54,560 --> 00:28:56,200
Compared to our workshop's,

640
00:28:56,520 --> 00:28:57,480
it's much finer.

641
00:28:58,600 --> 00:29:00,200
Because it's thin,

642
00:29:01,160 --> 00:29:04,480
it requires an even finer pulp.

643
00:29:05,400 --> 00:29:06,800
But to make it any finer,

644
00:29:06,800 --> 00:29:08,880
we'd have to use a soy milk grinder.

645
00:29:10,600 --> 00:29:11,680
If we did that,

646
00:29:12,080 --> 00:29:14,840
the fiber structure would be destroyed.

647
00:29:15,160 --> 00:29:15,960
Zhang Du.

648
00:29:17,000 --> 00:29:19,720
Didn't we prepare a batch of scorched bark?

649
00:29:20,560 --> 00:29:21,600
Tomorrow,

650
00:29:23,720 --> 00:29:25,000
let's pound it once more.

651
00:29:26,000 --> 00:29:27,000
I'll go do it right now.

652
00:29:27,000 --> 00:29:28,160
So it won't delay tomorrow's scooping.

653
00:29:28,520 --> 00:29:30,960
Enough, look at the time. Tomorrow.

654
00:29:31,000 --> 00:29:32,480
It's fine, Ma'am, I'm not tired.

655
00:29:36,000 --> 00:29:37,440
The moment paper-scooping is mentioned,

656
00:29:37,840 --> 00:29:39,000
his eyes light up.

657
00:31:21,280 --> 00:31:23,520
Zhang Du didn't sleep all night.

658
00:31:24,560 --> 00:31:26,920
He barely ate dinner last night either.

659
00:31:26,920 --> 00:31:28,240
He was busy working.

660
00:31:28,520 --> 00:31:29,320
Tell you what.

661
00:31:29,960 --> 00:31:31,160
You two go take a walk.

662
00:31:31,160 --> 00:31:33,440
I'll go make him some breakfast.

663
00:31:34,240 --> 00:31:35,000
Take it slow.

664
00:31:47,200 --> 00:31:49,240
It reminds me of what our ancestors

665
00:31:50,240 --> 00:31:52,440
once said in two lines.

666
00:31:52,800 --> 00:31:54,800
"A thousand poundings of jade yield stardust,"

667
00:31:55,120 --> 00:31:57,600
"one sheet of pure heart reveals the void."

668
00:31:57,960 --> 00:31:58,760
Tell me,

669
00:31:59,920 --> 00:32:02,920
what does "a thousand poundings of jade" mean?

670
00:32:03,360 --> 00:32:05,760
What does "one sheet of pure heart" mean?

671
00:32:11,160 --> 00:32:13,960
Lao Xuan, isn't this it?

672
00:32:14,760 --> 00:32:16,640
You've got yourself a fine apprentice.

673
00:32:17,160 --> 00:32:17,960
All right.

674
00:32:19,000 --> 00:32:19,840
Xuan Yan.

675
00:32:22,440 --> 00:32:23,440
I'm sorry.

676
00:32:23,720 --> 00:32:24,480
I didn't earn you any money.

677
00:32:24,480 --> 00:32:25,760
And I ruined your event.

678
00:32:25,840 --> 00:32:28,040
It's fine. That was all VP Zhang's doing.

679
00:32:28,040 --> 00:32:30,240
Don't take everything on yourself.

680
00:32:30,720 --> 00:32:31,920
I figured

681
00:32:32,560 --> 00:32:33,840
you probably needed some comfort,

682
00:32:33,840 --> 00:32:35,160
so I bought some snacks.

683
00:32:35,160 --> 00:32:36,440
I was just about to text you

684
00:32:36,440 --> 00:32:37,280
to cheer you up.

685
00:32:37,280 --> 00:32:37,960
Look at you,

686
00:32:39,640 --> 00:32:41,160
so strong on the inside.

687
00:32:41,560 --> 00:32:43,040
Then I can rest easy.

688
00:32:43,920 --> 00:32:44,720
So, how's it going?

689
00:32:44,960 --> 00:32:46,160
Did you find the cause?

690
00:32:46,880 --> 00:32:47,800
I haven't.

691
00:32:48,520 --> 00:32:49,800
But you must have,

692
00:32:50,120 --> 00:32:51,360
otherwise why would you come to me?

693
00:32:53,120 --> 00:32:55,840
Then as your partner,

694
00:32:55,840 --> 00:32:57,080
let me have a word with you, okay?

695
00:32:57,120 --> 00:32:58,720
You can absolutely, as the boss,

696
00:32:58,720 --> 00:32:59,680
give me some orders.

697
00:33:00,000 --> 00:33:01,120
Then I'll shut up.

698
00:33:01,200 --> 00:33:02,840
Delivery's done, I'm heading out.

699
00:33:02,840 --> 00:33:04,400
No, no, no. Partner, partner.

700
00:33:04,920 --> 00:33:05,560
Coffee?

701
00:33:05,720 --> 00:33:06,040
Sure.

702
00:33:06,040 --> 00:33:06,680
All right then.

703
00:33:17,840 --> 00:33:18,560
Xuan Yan.

704
00:33:19,080 --> 00:33:20,320
To be honest with you,

705
00:33:20,920 --> 00:33:22,920
as a designer,

706
00:33:23,560 --> 00:33:25,680
you're too much of a designer.

707
00:33:26,760 --> 00:33:27,520
You

708
00:33:27,800 --> 00:33:28,920
expect consumers

709
00:33:28,920 --> 00:33:30,720
to understand your design philosophy,

710
00:33:30,720 --> 00:33:32,520
and resonate on the same wavelength.

711
00:33:32,960 --> 00:33:34,960
But what consumers really want to buy

712
00:33:34,960 --> 00:33:37,200
is never about understanding others,

713
00:33:37,400 --> 00:33:39,440
but being understood by others.

714
00:33:40,240 --> 00:33:43,160
Take the wooden box album we made.

715
00:33:43,560 --> 00:33:44,680
Inside it

716
00:33:44,840 --> 00:33:47,480
are your reflections on life, right?

717
00:33:47,480 --> 00:33:48,760
Your understanding of life.

718
00:33:49,080 --> 00:33:50,880
Anyone who grasps this point

719
00:33:51,160 --> 00:33:52,200
will feel,

720
00:33:52,600 --> 00:33:54,520
"This hits me right in the heart."

721
00:33:54,520 --> 00:33:56,960
So they're willing to pay a high price for it.

722
00:33:59,720 --> 00:34:02,240
But with cultural products,

723
00:34:02,840 --> 00:34:04,840
we go through mass-market channels.

724
00:34:04,840 --> 00:34:05,840
What we can leverage

725
00:34:05,840 --> 00:34:07,680
is only the mass market.

726
00:34:08,000 --> 00:34:10,320
So strictly speaking,

727
00:34:11,480 --> 00:34:13,000
we make products,

728
00:34:13,000 --> 00:34:14,080
not art pieces.

729
00:34:15,760 --> 00:34:17,159
I get what you mean.

730
00:34:18,520 --> 00:34:19,600
You're saying

731
00:34:20,560 --> 00:34:22,000
I'm still too pretentious,

732
00:34:22,040 --> 00:34:23,400
I haven't brought myself down to earth.

733
00:34:25,239 --> 00:34:26,320
What's going on?

734
00:34:27,760 --> 00:34:28,600
What's wrong?

735
00:34:31,199 --> 00:34:31,920
Creases.

736
00:34:32,560 --> 00:34:33,560
Two lines would be normal.

737
00:34:34,840 --> 00:34:35,840
This isn't normal.

738
00:34:37,040 --> 00:34:38,239
Every single sheet has them.

739
00:34:41,360 --> 00:34:42,480
You're right.

740
00:34:46,440 --> 00:34:47,040
Xuan Yan.

741
00:34:47,520 --> 00:34:49,080
Actually, your talent

742
00:34:49,080 --> 00:34:50,040
is beyond question.

743
00:34:50,159 --> 00:34:50,960
If

744
00:34:51,239 --> 00:34:53,080
you didn't go down the commercial path,

745
00:34:53,080 --> 00:34:54,239
you'd actually be

746
00:34:54,239 --> 00:34:56,679
an outstanding, independent designer.

747
00:34:56,920 --> 00:34:57,720
But

748
00:34:58,000 --> 00:35:00,840
you've already chosen the industry path.

749
00:35:00,960 --> 00:35:04,000
So you have to learn to speak to the masses.

750
00:35:04,160 --> 00:35:06,480
Sometimes a certain degree of compromise

751
00:35:06,480 --> 00:35:07,960
is truly necessary.

752
00:35:08,320 --> 00:35:09,160
However,

753
00:35:09,760 --> 00:35:12,080
compromise isn't surrender.

754
00:35:12,160 --> 00:35:13,240
We're just

755
00:35:13,440 --> 00:35:14,920
switching battlefields.

756
00:35:16,280 --> 00:35:17,640
You don't need to comfort me.

757
00:35:18,000 --> 00:35:19,040
I just feel

758
00:35:19,560 --> 00:35:21,640
like it wasn't VP Zhang who took that punch,

759
00:35:21,640 --> 00:35:22,440
but me.

760
00:35:23,240 --> 00:35:24,560
That's totally normal.

761
00:35:24,560 --> 00:35:26,360
Anyone called out like that

762
00:35:26,360 --> 00:35:28,000
would be stunned for a while.

763
00:35:31,320 --> 00:35:33,040
Won't brushing like that damage it?

764
00:35:33,240 --> 00:35:35,560
It's my first time seeing this technique.

765
00:35:35,840 --> 00:35:36,800
How fascinating.

766
00:35:41,160 --> 00:35:43,200
Hongxing Factory handles many tasks each year.

767
00:35:43,480 --> 00:35:45,600
We've seen all kinds of strange things.

768
00:35:45,600 --> 00:35:46,600
Nothing surprises us anymore.

769
00:35:46,640 --> 00:35:47,360
In a little while,

770
00:35:47,360 --> 00:35:49,600
every time Master Ye scoops two or three sheets,

771
00:35:49,800 --> 00:35:50,560
you two stay right here

772
00:35:50,560 --> 00:35:52,800
and gently wipe it down the way I just showed you.

773
00:35:52,960 --> 00:35:54,360
That'll guarantee there are no problems.

774
00:35:55,280 --> 00:35:56,960
So what's the principle behind this?

775
00:35:57,280 --> 00:35:58,480
Since the day before yesterday,

776
00:35:58,600 --> 00:35:59,960
the weather has turned colder.

777
00:36:00,440 --> 00:36:02,120
We added a lot of kiwi vine juice.

778
00:36:02,280 --> 00:36:03,840
Once the temperature gets too low,

779
00:36:04,000 --> 00:36:06,440
the water permeability weakens.

780
00:36:07,000 --> 00:36:09,200
Water droplets cling to the bamboo screen,

781
00:36:09,600 --> 00:36:12,760
which easily causes wrinkles and water holes.

782
00:36:14,480 --> 00:36:16,600
The cultural products I designed before,

783
00:36:16,600 --> 00:36:17,720
have you seen them?

784
00:36:20,320 --> 00:36:21,440
I've seen every one.

785
00:36:22,280 --> 00:36:23,200
None of them work.

786
00:36:26,200 --> 00:36:28,600
I think all your previous products

787
00:36:28,600 --> 00:36:31,320
were created based on one design logic,

788
00:36:31,640 --> 00:36:34,000
which is waiting to be understood.

789
00:36:34,360 --> 00:36:36,360
But what's the logic of the market?

790
00:36:36,360 --> 00:36:37,920
It's that you have to actively understand them.

791
00:36:42,520 --> 00:36:44,000
I'm reminded of a famous quote.

792
00:36:44,400 --> 00:36:46,520
The you in others' eyes isn't you.

793
00:36:47,120 --> 00:36:49,320
The you in your own eyes isn't you.

794
00:36:49,600 --> 00:36:51,720
The others in your eyes—that's who you are.

795
00:36:52,800 --> 00:36:54,000
Got you tangled up, didn't it?

796
00:36:55,560 --> 00:36:56,960
I hope what I just said

797
00:36:57,080 --> 00:36:58,320
was only a friendly reminder,

798
00:36:58,320 --> 00:36:59,520
and didn't hurt your feelings.

799
00:37:00,920 --> 00:37:02,000
No, it's not that bad.

800
00:37:02,440 --> 00:37:03,200
Don't worry.

801
00:37:03,720 --> 00:37:04,720
I'll change.

802
00:37:13,640 --> 00:37:14,920
Twelve grams per sheet.

803
00:37:15,440 --> 00:37:16,680
That's two grams too heavy.

804
00:37:17,520 --> 00:37:19,320
The physical and chemical indicators all meet the standard.

805
00:37:19,520 --> 00:37:20,640
It's just the weight issue.

806
00:37:22,120 --> 00:37:23,240
For a four-foot sheet,

807
00:37:23,920 --> 00:37:25,640
if we can keep it at ten grams,

808
00:37:26,520 --> 00:37:27,880
the thickness won't be a problem.

809
00:37:28,560 --> 00:37:30,600
Don't underestimate those two grams.

810
00:37:31,600 --> 00:37:33,280
If you want to bring it down,

811
00:37:35,160 --> 00:37:36,600
it's extremely difficult.

812
00:37:40,640 --> 00:37:41,440
Master,

813
00:37:41,880 --> 00:37:43,000
give me a few days.

814
00:37:43,560 --> 00:37:45,480
I'll find a way to bring it down.

815
00:37:56,200 --> 00:37:56,960
Almost done.

816
00:38:04,440 --> 00:38:07,200
How can our master paper-dryer

817
00:38:07,200 --> 00:38:08,000
be doing this kind of work?

818
00:38:08,000 --> 00:38:09,040
Move aside, let me do it.

819
00:38:09,040 --> 00:38:10,520
No need, Sister Xiumei.

820
00:38:10,520 --> 00:38:12,400
Just let him show off a little.

821
00:38:12,520 --> 00:38:13,360
Sister Xiumei,

822
00:38:13,640 --> 00:38:14,960
my cooking skills

823
00:38:14,960 --> 00:38:16,120
are no worse than my paper-drying.

824
00:38:16,400 --> 00:38:18,120
Look, see that?

825
00:38:18,120 --> 00:38:19,280
He's even flipping the wok!

826
00:38:19,280 --> 00:38:20,360
I can tell.

827
00:38:20,360 --> 00:38:21,960
Color, aroma, and flavor, all there.

828
00:38:21,960 --> 00:38:22,520
Right.

829
00:38:22,720 --> 00:38:24,120
Look at our Xuan family men,

830
00:38:24,320 --> 00:38:26,520
handling both indoors and outdoors.

831
00:38:27,480 --> 00:38:29,560
The thinnest sheet in this batch is 10.9 grams.

832
00:38:30,720 --> 00:38:31,640
How many sheets in total?

833
00:38:32,520 --> 00:38:34,640
Currently, those under 11 grams,

834
00:38:34,640 --> 00:38:35,640
we only have these seven.

835
00:38:37,560 --> 00:38:39,280
The thinnest is 10.9 grams.

836
00:38:42,520 --> 00:38:43,320
Yongnian,

837
00:38:44,560 --> 00:38:45,520
if it doesn't work out,

838
00:38:46,040 --> 00:38:48,720
have Lao Man and Master Ye scoop a few.

839
00:38:51,040 --> 00:38:51,640
Lao Man, have a seat.

840
00:38:51,640 --> 00:38:52,280
Okay.

841
00:38:52,760 --> 00:38:53,560
Okay.

842
00:38:54,000 --> 00:38:55,080
Lao Xuan,

843
00:38:55,520 --> 00:38:56,920
I've been so anxious,

844
00:38:57,120 --> 00:38:59,080
my mouth's about to break out in blisters.

845
00:38:59,640 --> 00:39:00,400
Just think about it,

846
00:39:00,840 --> 00:39:03,160
making Chengxintang paper is such a huge deal,

847
00:39:03,400 --> 00:39:06,200
it's not the time for Zhang Du to practice.

848
00:39:06,520 --> 00:39:07,960
By the time he's mastered it,

849
00:39:08,120 --> 00:39:10,000
who knows when that'll be?

850
00:39:12,440 --> 00:39:13,520
Don't be anxious.

851
00:39:13,880 --> 00:39:15,440
Being anxious won't help.

852
00:39:16,520 --> 00:39:17,440
Tell me,

853
00:39:18,520 --> 00:39:19,600
if we replace Zhang Du,

854
00:39:20,000 --> 00:39:21,440
would he agree?

855
00:39:21,840 --> 00:39:23,120
If he'd agree,

856
00:39:23,400 --> 00:39:25,000
we wouldn't be coming to you.

857
00:39:25,120 --> 00:39:26,080
Right.

858
00:39:26,440 --> 00:39:28,160
Zhang Du, that young man,

859
00:39:29,960 --> 00:39:31,000
he's sincere.

860
00:39:31,640 --> 00:39:32,880
At such a critical moment,

861
00:39:32,880 --> 00:39:34,160
if you replace him,

862
00:39:34,600 --> 00:39:36,440
it would really hurt him.

863
00:39:37,360 --> 00:39:38,920
Lao Man's chief engineer at Hongxing Factory.

864
00:39:38,920 --> 00:39:40,040
He understands best.

865
00:39:40,520 --> 00:39:42,400
How many young people nowadays

866
00:39:42,400 --> 00:39:44,720
love paper the way Zhang Du does?

867
00:39:46,880 --> 00:39:49,600
It's not easy to train one.

868
00:39:50,680 --> 00:39:51,400
That's true.

869
00:39:51,680 --> 00:39:53,880
Xiao Man is honest

870
00:39:54,520 --> 00:39:56,120
and can be patient too.

871
00:39:56,320 --> 00:39:57,960
But compared to Zhang Du,

872
00:39:58,320 --> 00:40:00,600
he lacks diligence and dedication.

873
00:40:01,720 --> 00:40:04,280
But this takes time and skill.

874
00:40:04,640 --> 00:40:06,640
Give Zhang Du a little more time.

875
00:40:06,840 --> 00:40:07,880
But doing this

876
00:40:07,880 --> 00:40:10,560
would delay your schedule.

877
00:40:10,560 --> 00:40:11,680
That's not a problem.

878
00:40:12,280 --> 00:40:14,560
I'd be glad to help him along.

879
00:40:20,720 --> 00:40:22,320
Your hands are in such bad shape

880
00:40:23,000 --> 00:40:24,320
and you don't say a word.

881
00:40:25,440 --> 00:40:26,240
It hurts, doesn't it?

882
00:40:27,040 --> 00:40:28,720
It doesn't hurt, ma'am. I'm fine.

883
00:40:28,800 --> 00:40:30,280
Not hurting, my foot.

884
00:40:30,880 --> 00:40:31,840
Let me tell you,

885
00:40:32,440 --> 00:40:33,960
once you put ointment on your hands

886
00:40:34,320 --> 00:40:35,680
and then dip them in the lye water,

887
00:40:35,720 --> 00:40:37,120
it's like you never applied any.

888
00:40:38,000 --> 00:40:39,080
Listen to me,

889
00:40:39,680 --> 00:40:40,520
take a couple of days off.

890
00:40:41,200 --> 00:40:42,080
Stop working.

891
00:40:43,080 --> 00:40:44,360
I can't rest, ma'am.

892
00:40:44,640 --> 00:40:46,040
We're almost there.

893
00:40:46,440 --> 00:40:48,160
So what if you succeed?

894
00:40:48,280 --> 00:40:49,600
What does it have to do with you?

895
00:40:50,200 --> 00:40:51,440
What do you gain from it?

896
00:40:52,680 --> 00:40:53,520
Stop it.

897
00:40:54,120 --> 00:40:56,600
I'll tell Lao Man and Master Ye later,

898
00:40:56,600 --> 00:40:57,640
let them handle it.

899
00:40:58,320 --> 00:40:59,360
No, ma'am.

900
00:40:59,920 --> 00:41:01,120
Chengxintang paper

901
00:41:01,280 --> 00:41:03,120
must be scooped out by

902
00:41:03,120 --> 00:41:04,480
someone from our own Xuan family.

903
00:41:07,520 --> 00:41:09,680
Just as stubborn as your master.

904
00:41:15,760 --> 00:41:17,200
Don't put them in water again, all right?

905
00:41:17,880 --> 00:41:19,040
Ma'am, the ointment...

906
00:41:19,800 --> 00:41:20,800
Keep it and use it.

907
00:41:21,120 --> 00:41:22,200
If it's not enough, tell me,

908
00:41:22,200 --> 00:41:23,360
I'll buy you more.

909
00:41:24,600 --> 00:41:25,520
Thank you, ma'am.

910
00:41:26,480 --> 00:41:27,960
Xiao Yu, Xiao Man,

911
00:41:28,520 --> 00:41:29,960
you two do a bit more.

912
00:41:30,040 --> 00:41:32,160
Look at the state of Zhang Du's hands.

913
00:41:32,480 --> 00:41:33,320
Stop fooling around.

914
00:41:33,520 --> 00:41:34,200
Sure thing, ma'am.

915
00:41:34,200 --> 00:41:35,120
It's all right, ma'am.

916
00:41:46,160 --> 00:41:46,720
Okay.

917
00:41:59,560 --> 00:42:00,360
Master Ye,

918
00:42:00,640 --> 00:42:02,600
go a bit lighter on the second scoop.

919
00:42:20,640 --> 00:42:21,680
Thanks, driver.

920
00:42:24,920 --> 00:42:26,120
Taozi, how's it going?

921
00:42:26,520 --> 00:42:27,680
We've got enough footage,

922
00:42:27,800 --> 00:42:29,080
but I have to say,

923
00:42:29,160 --> 00:42:30,520
Zhang Du is unbelievable.

924
00:42:31,200 --> 00:42:32,920
Three days and nights without sleep.

925
00:42:33,040 --> 00:42:33,840
Three days?

926
00:42:34,920 --> 00:42:35,880
Is he insane?

927
00:42:54,920 --> 00:42:55,680
Zhang Du!

928
00:42:57,240 --> 00:42:57,720
Zhang Du!
